      <prov id="DLM186250" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">258A</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Conditions on course approvals</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Every course approval is subject to the condition that the institution will at all times comply with the relevant policies and criteria established by the Authority under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186208">section 253(1)(d)</intref></citation> that are currently in force, except to the extent that the Authority exempts the institution, by a condition on the approval, from compliance.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>When approving a course, the Authority may impose conditions on the approval that are specific to the approval for that particular course.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Authority may at any time, with the agreement of the institution that holds the course approval, impose new conditions on the approval and may amend or revoke any existing conditions.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Authority may, without the agreement of the institution, impose conditions on a course approval, or amend or revoke any existing conditions, but only if the Authority has first—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>given written notice to the institution of its intentions; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>given the institution a reasonable opportunity to respond to the notice; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>considered any submissions made by the institution in response to the notice.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>When conditions are imposed, amended, or revoked, the Authority must give notice in writing to the institution that holds the approval of the new, amended, or revoked conditions.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186251"><amended-provision>Section 258A</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>inserted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166219">section 36</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186252" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">259</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Accreditation <insertwords>to provide</insertwords> approved courses</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>This section has effect subject to <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186264">section 260</intref></citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1A</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>In this section, <def-term id="DLM186253" xml:lang="en-NZ">institution</def-term> means an institution, government training establishment, registered establishment, or secondary school.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>An institution<struckoutwords/> that proposes to provide an approved course of study or training may apply to the Authority for the grant of accreditation to provide that course.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Authority may grant or refuse accreditation to an institution<struckoutwords/> to provide an approved course.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Accreditation may be granted without limitation as to time or for a specified period.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If the Authority considers that there may be grounds for withdrawing an accreditation from an institution, the Authority must give written notice to the governing body of the institution—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>setting out the grounds on which the Authority is considering withdrawing the approval; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>giving the governing body of the institution a reasonable period within which to make submissions on the matter.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>After that period and having considered any submission made by the<struckoutwords/> governing body, the Authority may, on reasonable grounds, withdraw the accreditation.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">7</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If the Authority withdraws an accreditation under this section, it must give notice of the withdrawal, with reasons, to the institution concerned.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">8</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Nothing in this section limits the Authority's power to withdraw an accreditation under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186232">section 255A(7)</intref></citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186254"><amended-provision>Section 259</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186255"><amended-provision>Section 259 heading</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118496">section 54(1)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186256"><amended-provision>Section 259(1A)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>inserted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118496">section 54(2)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186258"><amended-provision>Section 259(2)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118496">section 54(3)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM1892207"><amended-provision>Section 259(3)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118496">section 54(4)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186259"><amended-provision>Section 259(5)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>substituted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118496">section 54(5)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186260"><amended-provision>Section 259(6)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118496">section 54(6)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186261"><amended-provision>Section 259(7)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166221">section 37</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM1892209"><amended-provision>Section 259(8)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166221">section 37</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186262" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">259A</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Conditions on accreditation to provide approved courses</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Every accreditation is subject to the condition that the institution will at all times comply with the relevant policies and criteria established by the Authority under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186208">section 253(1)(e)</intref></citation> that are currently in force, except to the extent that the Authority exempts the institution, by a condition on the accreditation, from compliance.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>When granting accreditation to an institution to provide an approved course of study or training, the Authority may impose conditions on the accreditation that are specific to the accreditation.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Authority may at any time, with the agreement of the accredited institution, impose new conditions on the accreditation and may amend or revoke any existing conditions.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Authority may, without the agreement of the institution, impose conditions on an accreditation, or amend or revoke any existing conditions, but only if the Authority has first—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>given written notice to the institution of its intentions; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>given the institution a reasonable opportunity to respond to the notice; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>considered any submissions made by the institution in response to the notice.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>When conditions are imposed, amended, or revoked, the Authority must give notice in writing to the accredited institution of the new, amended, or revoked conditions.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186263"><amended-provision>Section 259A</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>inserted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166222">section 38</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186264" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">260</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Exercise of certain powers of Authority</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The powers of the Authority under <insertwords><citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186232">sections 255A</intref>, <intref href="DLM186239">258</intref>, <intref href="DLM186250">258A</intref>, <intref href="DLM186252">259</intref>, and <intref href="DLM186262">259A</intref></citation></insertwords> in so far as they apply in relation to universities are, subject to this section, exercisable by the Vice-Chancellors Committee in lieu of the Authority, and references in those sections to the Authority shall, in the application of those sections to universities, be read as references to that Committee.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Where there is a body established by institutions, or by a class of institutions, other than universities for the purpose, or for purposes that include the purpose, of exercising the powers of the Authority under <insertwords><citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186232">sections 255A</intref>, <intref href="DLM186239">258</intref>, <intref href="DLM186250">258A</intref>, <intref href="DLM186252">259</intref>, and <intref href="DLM186262">259A</intref></citation></insertwords>,—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>the Authority may by writing delegate to that body the powers of the Authority under <insertwords><citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186232">sections 255A</intref>, <intref href="DLM186239">258</intref>, <intref href="DLM186250">258A</intref>, <intref href="DLM186252">259</intref>, and <intref href="DLM186262">259A</intref></citation></insertwords> in relation to those institutions or institutions of that class, as the case may be; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>while the delegation is in force, references in <insertwords><citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186232">sections 255A</intref>, <intref href="DLM186239">258</intref>, <intref href="DLM186250">258A</intref>, <intref href="DLM186252">259</intref>, and <intref href="DLM186262">259A</intref></citation></insertwords> to the Authority shall, in the application of those sections to the institutions or class of institutions to which the delegation relates, be read as references to that body.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>A body exercising powers pursuant to subsection (1) or subsection (2) shall, in exercising those powers, apply the criteria established by the Authority under <citation jurisdiction="nz">paragraphs (d) and (e) of <intref href="DLM186208">section 253(1)</intref></citation>.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If the Authority is of the opinion on reasonable grounds that a body exercising powers pursuant to subsection (1) or subsection (2) may not be applying the criteria referred to in subsection (3), the Authority may give written notice to the body—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>stating that it is of that opinion; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>setting out the reasons why the Authority is of that opinion; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>giving the body a reasonable opportunity to consult the Authority as to the way in which the powers have been exercised by the body,—</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <text>and shall consider any views expressed by the body.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If, after it has complied with subsection (4) in respect of a body, the Authority is satisfied that the body is not applying the criteria referred to in subsection (3), the Authority may give a written direction to the body to apply those criteria.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If, after the Authority has given a direction to a body under subsection (5), the Authority is satisfied that the body has failed to comply with the direction, the Authority shall submit a written report on the matter to the Minister.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">7</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Minister shall lay the report before the House of Representatives as soon as practicable after the report is received by the Minister.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">8</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If, in the case of a report relating to a body other than the Vice-Chancellors Committee, the Authority is satisfied after the end of a reasonable period after the report is laid before the House of Representatives that the body is still not complying with the direction given to it under subsection (5), the Authority may, by notice in writing to the body, revoke the delegation given to the body under subsection (2).</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">9</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>A delegation under subsection (2) continues in force unless and until it is revoked under subsection (8).</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">10</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>A delegation under subsection (2) to a body that is not a corporation is a delegation to the persons from time to time constituting the body.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">11</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Vice-Chancellors Committee or a body to which powers are delegated under subsection (2) may charge fees to an institution for the grant of any approval or accreditation.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186265"><amended-provision>Section 260</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186266"><amended-provision>Section 260(1)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166224">section 39</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM1892212"><amended-provision>Section 260(2)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166224">section 39</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM2170200"><amended-provision>Section 260(2)(a)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166224">section 39</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM2170202"><amended-provision>Section 260(2)(b)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166224">section 39</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186267" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">261</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Only accredited institutions<struckoutwords/> to provide approved courses</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>An institution <insertwords>(as defined in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186252">section 259(1A)</intref></citation>)</insertwords> does not have power to provide an approved course of study or training unless the institution<struckoutwords/> is accredited to provide that course.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186268"><amended-provision>Section 261</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186269"><amended-provision>Section 261 heading</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118874">section 82(1)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186270"><amended-provision>Section 261</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118874">section 82(1)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186271" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">262</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Notice</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Authority, the Vice-Chancellors Committee, or a body to which powers have been delegated by the Authority under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186264">section 260(2)</intref></citation>, as the case requires, shall give to an institution or private training establishment written notice of the grant, refusal or withdrawal of approval of a course of study or training provided or to be provided at the institution or establishment, or of accreditation of the institution or establishment to provide an approved course of study or training, as soon as practicable after the decision to grant, refuse, or withdraw the approval or accreditation is made.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>A notice of the refusal or withdrawal of approval or accreditation shall set out the reasons for the refusal or withdrawal.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186272"><amended-provision>Section 262</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186273" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">263</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Awards for approved nationally recognised courses</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>When an institution <insertwords>(as defined in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186252">section 259(1A)</intref></citation>)</insertwords> provides an approved nationally recognised course that the institution<struckoutwords/> is accredited to provide, the institution<struckoutwords/>, or the Authority, may, subject to this Act, grant an award to a person who has completed the course stating that the course was an approved nationally recognised course.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186274"><amended-provision>Section 263</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186275"><amended-provision>Section 263</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118874">section 82(1)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186277" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">264</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Applications for consents by Authority</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>A person may apply to the Authority for its consent—</text>
              <label-para deletion-status="repealed" skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para>
                  <text/>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>to grant an award that is described as a degree or the description of which includes the word bachelor, master or doctor.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Subject to <struckoutwords/><citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186216">section 254</intref></citation>, the Authority may grant or refuse its consent.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov deletion-status="repealed" skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text/>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186278"><amended-provision>Section 264</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186279"><amended-provision>Section 264(1)(a)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>repealed</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118498">section 55(1)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186280"><amended-provision>Section 264(2)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118498">section 55(2)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186281"><amended-provision>Section 264(3)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>repealed</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118498">section 55(3)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186282" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">264A</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Minister may consent to registered establishments using certain terms in their names</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>A registered establishment may apply to the Minister for consent to use the term university, college of education, polytechnic, or institute of technology to describe a registered establishment that is not an institution.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Before deciding whether to give consent under subsection (1), the Minister must—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>take into account the characteristics of institutions as described in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM183668">section 162(4)</intref></citation>; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>receive advice on the application from the Authority; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">ba</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>be satisfied that consenting to the application is in the interests of the tertiary education system and the nation as a whole; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">c</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>consult with the institutions, organisations representing institutions, and other relevant bodies that the Minister considers appropriate.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>In deciding whether to give consent under subsection (1) to the use of the term institute of technology, the relevant characteristics that the Minister must take into account are the characteristics of a polytechnic.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Minister may audit any registered establishment that has been given consent to use one of the terms in subsection (1) for continuous compliance with the requirements for consent to use the term.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">5</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>If the Minister is not satisfied that a registered establishment is continuing to comply with the requirements for consent to use the term for which consent has been given, the Minister may—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>withdraw the consent; or</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>suspend the consent for a specified period, at the expiry of which the Minster must either lift the suspension or withdraw the consent.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186283"><amended-provision>Section 264A</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>inserted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118499">section 56</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186284"><amended-provision>Section 264A(2)(ba)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>inserted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166225">section 40(1)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186285"><amended-provision>Section 264A(4)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166225">section 40(2)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM1892218"><amended-provision>Section 264A(5)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>1 January 2003</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM166225">section 40(2)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education (Tertiary Reform) Amendment Act 2002</amending-leg> (2002 No 50).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186286" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">265</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Examination and assessment</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Authority may, in accordance with such rules and procedures as it considers appropriate, set and conduct such examinations, and make such assessments, as it considers necessary for the performance of its functions.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>For the purposes of such examinations and assessments, the Authority may make regulations, give directions and approve examiners, assessors and moderators, and may grant awards to persons who reach such standards in the examinations or assessments as are set by the Authority.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Until 1 February 1991, any examinations that the Authority sets and conducts under this section shall be set and conducted, and any assessments that the Authority makes under this section shall be made, in accordance with the rules and procedures applicable immediately before the commencement of this section.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>Nothing in this Act permits the Authority, without the consent of the chief executive of the institution concerned, to set or conduct any examination, or make any assessment, in respect of the performance by any student in a course of study or training at an institution.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186287"><amended-provision>Section 265</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186288" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">266</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Fees</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>The Authority may—</text>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>charge fees to an institution <insertwords>(as defined in <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM186239">section 258(1A)</intref> or <intref href="DLM186252">section 259(1A)</intref></citation>, as appropriate)</insertwords> for the grant of any approval or accreditation; and</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
              <label-para skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
                <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
                  <text>charge fees to any person for any services provided by the Authority, including fees in relation to sitting for an examination conducted by the Authority, in relation to the making of any assessment by the Authority or in relation to the granting to any person of an award certifying that the person had passed such an examination or been so assessed.</text>
                </para>
              </label-para>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>A fee may not be charged under subsection (1)(b) to a person who is a student at a secondary school unless the Minister has consented to the charging of the fee.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186289"><amended-provision>Section 266</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186290"><amended-provision>Section 266(1)(a)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 October 2001</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM118874">section 82(1)</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Standards Act 2001</amending-leg> (2001 No 88).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186291" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">267</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Saving of certain statutes, etc, of University of New Zealand</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="no"/>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>All statutes, regulations, rulings, decisions, and other acts of authority of the Senate of the University of New Zealand or any committee or board of that Senate or University, or of the Chancellor, Vice-Chancellor or any officer of that University, so far as they relate to the University Entrance Examination and were in force immediately before the commencement of this section by virtue of <citation jurisdiction="nz">section 45 of the Universities Act 1961</citation>, continue in force except so far as they are repealed, replaced, or amended by any enactment or by regulations, rulings, decisions, or other acts of authority of the Qualifications Authority or of the Council of any university under powers conferred by this Act or any other enactment.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186292"><amended-provision>Section 267</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
      <prov id="DLM186293" irdnumbering="no" skeleton="no" toc="yes" xml:lang="en-NZ">
        <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">268</label>
        <heading xml:lang="en-NZ">Powers of Minister</heading>
        <prov.body>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text>In the performance of its functions under this Part, the Authority shall not establish any policy in relation to the systems of evaluation, assessment, or certification of the ability or achievement of students at secondary schools unless the Minister has approved that policy in writing.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
            <para xml:lang="en-NZ">
              <text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM330351">Section 103</extref> of the Crown Entities Act 2004</citation> applies in the performance of the Authority's functions under this Part.</text>
            </para>
          </subprov>
          <subprov deletion-status="repealed" skeleton="no" xml:lang="en-NZ">
            <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
            <para>
              <text/>
            </para>
          </subprov>
        </prov.body>
        <notes>
          <history>
            <history-note id="DLM186294"><amended-provision>Section 268</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>added</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>23 July 1990</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM212667">section 42</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Education Amendment Act 1990</amending-leg> (1990 No 60).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186295"><amended-provision>Section 268(2)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>substituted</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 January 2005</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM331111">section 200</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Crown Entities Act 2004</amending-leg> (2004 No 115).</history-note>
            <history-note id="DLM186296"><amended-provision>Section 268(3)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>repealed</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 January 2005</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM331111">section 200</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Crown Entities Act 2004</amending-leg> (2004 No 115).</history-note>
          </history>
        </notes>
      </prov>
    </part>
